6:
No! No, I—I mean, um...I!
 NEVER MIND! BYE!
10:
Princess, now is the time to strike! You 
can't run, not when you're this close!
18:
Now you go talk to the nice gentleman 
RIGHT NOW. Do you hear me, young 
lady?
31:
I... I LIKE YOU!
I really, really like you! A lot!
33:
So, um, p-please be my...you know... 
My boyfriend!
37:
Thank you for telling me and...
Please accept my apologies.
40:
While I am flattered, I am afraid 
I cannot reciprocate your feelings.
44:
W-why not? Because you are human, 
and I, yokai?
47: No, I assure you, that is not the reason.
51:
Theb why?! *sniffle* Ish it b-becub—
WAAAAAH!
58:
It's for the best, dearie. This was bound 
to happen sooner or later. Besides, her 
mother never would have approved.
59:
Princess Inaho is much too good a girl 
to waste upon some human.
63:
Soushiro, man, your timing couldn't 
have sucked more! Ahaha!
66:
Perhaps, but I am afraid there are 
more pressing matters at hand; I must 
speak with Stella. She—
69:
She?! Who, that human? Young man, 
it's not been a MINUTE since you broke 
poor Inaho's heart, and you're already 
chasing skirts?!
73:
Madam, I assure you I have no such 
intentions... There was something 
stuck to her back that resembled 
a shiki—
77:
Wait. Where is Stella? Was she not with 
you a moment ago?
84:
I couldb use a—hic—a liddle pat 
ondthe back... a-and maybe 
a scradge be-behind the ears…
93:
That is not what I meant! You have to 
pet my head gently AND ask me about 
it!
97:
Oh, I'm sorry. What am I supposed to 
ask you about?
101:
Uh, um... Why I like Soushiro? How long 
I have loved him? Just—Just, anything!
105:
Okay. Why do you like Soushiro? 
How long have you loved him?
110:
You, you truly wish to know? See, ever 
since I was a little kit, I have always 
loved visiting the mortal realm!
111:
I often played amongst humans, until 
one day I got caught in a hunter's 
trap! Soushiro saved me, and I have 
liked him ever since.
114:
Couldn't you escape on your own? 
You seem very powerful.
118:
Well, I am NOW, but not at the time. My 
powers were not fully developed yet.
120:
I was alone, trapped, and scared... And 
then, there he was, at my side! I have 
always wanted to thank him for 
helping me back then.
122: But now he... he probably hates me...
124:
Why would he hate you?
I think you are very likeable.
128:
I didn't understand what the others 
said about liking in a romantic way. 
Does it mean liking someone a lot? 
I like you a lot, Inaho.
131:
T-that is called "friendship!" It is very 
similar, but also very different!
133: I believe I've heard more than enough.
137:
You disrupted our peace and order 
over some silly crush? I was expecting 
a better excuse, but you will be 
exorcised nonetheless.
143:
You've already served your 
purpose.
...I must confess, you did an excellent 
job leading me to her.
156:
The diviners have Inaho! Suizen took 
her!
159: They can't have got far. Let's go!
